581
00:34:24.437 --> 00:34:27.897
Okay. The next speaker is Mariam Belabed from Mount

582
00:34:28.016 --> 00:34:31.906
Sinai. Start her presentation. Will

583
00:34:32.036 --> 00:34:35.086
discuss metabolic reuse of tumor-derived signals coordinates dendritic cell

584
00:34:35.156 --> 00:34:37.816
function. Please. Thank you.

585
00:34:42.756 --> 00:34:46.336
Good afternoon, everyone. So first, thanks to the organizers for this

586
00:34:46.377 --> 00:34:47.615
opportunity to present today.

587
00:34:48.457 --> 00:34:52.096
So for today's presentation, I'm going to discuss how dendritic cells

588
00:34:52.156 --> 00:34:56.016
repurpose tumor-derived metabolite to shape their function.

589
00:34:58.956 --> 00:35:02.816
So dendritic cells are essential to enhance adaptive immune response, but they are

590
00:35:02.896 --> 00:35:05.856
also very important during the anti-tumor immunity.

591
00:35:05.916 --> 00:35:09.696
They capture tumor antigen, process them, then migrate to the lymph node

592
00:35:09.816 --> 00:35:10.856
to prime T cells.

593
00:35:12.636 --> 00:35:16.396
And different preclinical studies demonstrated very well their importance.

594
00:35:16.436 --> 00:35:20.376
For example, here in this Batf3 knockout mouse model, which lacks dendritic

595
00:35:20.436 --> 00:35:24.256
cells type one, we can observe an increase in the tumor growth with this

596
00:35:24.336 --> 00:35:28.036
lung adenocarcinoma model, which highlight the importance of the

597
00:35:28.076 --> 00:35:29.996
cells during the anti-tumor immunity.

598
00:35:32.136 --> 00:35:35.676
So when immature dendritic cells uptake cellular or tumor-derived

599
00:35:35.736 --> 00:35:37.456
debris, they undergo maturation.

600
00:35:37.836 --> 00:35:41.396
And this maturation is characterized by the expression at the plasma

601
00:35:41.456 --> 00:35:45.196
membrane of different molecules that are important for their main

602
00:35:45.296 --> 00:35:48.996
function, for the antigen presentation, for the T cell activation and the

603
00:35:49.036 --> 00:35:52.356
regulation, but also for the migration to the lymph node through

604
00:35:52.396 --> 00:35:56.316
CCR7. And during my presentation, I will use CCR7 as an

605
00:35:56.356 --> 00:35:59.966
example to show the maturation state of the dendritic cells.

606
00:36:02.236 --> 00:36:05.636
However, the tumor-derived material is very heterogeneous and

607
00:36:05.696 --> 00:36:08.966
contains a wide range of signal, including metabolites.

608
00:36:09.356 --> 00:36:13.156
And here we ask whether the metabolites coming from the tumor can shape

609
00:36:13.476 --> 00:36:14.596
dendritic cells function.

610
00:36:16.316 --> 00:36:20.206
So from our metabolomic screen, the polyamines, putrescine, spermidine, and

611
00:36:20.256 --> 00:36:22.736
spermine, emerged as a key candidate.

612
00:36:23.016 --> 00:36:26.756
So they are generated through this pathway, and ODC1 plays a

613
00:36:26.816 --> 00:36:30.676
major role by converting ornithine into the first polyamine, which

614
00:36:30.736 --> 00:36:34.596
is putrescine. So to understand their function, we generated an

615
00:36:34.636 --> 00:36:38.456
ODC1 knockout tumor cell line. So it's a polyamine deficient tumor

616
00:36:38.536 --> 00:36:42.186
cell line. And we found that dendritic cells, when they

617
00:36:42.186 --> 00:36:45.916
uptake this ODC1 knockout tumor debris, the uptake is

618
00:36:45.996 --> 00:36:49.836
affected. They uptake less this ODC1 knockout tumor debris

619
00:36:49.876 --> 00:36:52.476
compared to the control, both in vivo and in

620
00:36:52.516 --> 00:36:56.344
vitro.And with this microscopy image, you can see in

621
00:36:56.384 --> 00:37:00.293
red dendritic cells on the top. They can uptake very well the wild type

622
00:37:00.344 --> 00:37:04.184
tumor debris, but for the ODC1 knockout, they can interact with them,

623
00:37:04.604 --> 00:37:06.164
but the uptake is less efficient.

624
00:37:07.724 --> 00:37:11.664
So then we asked whether the transfer of the polyamine into dendritic

625
00:37:11.724 --> 00:37:15.224
cells is important to regulate their uptake function.

626
00:37:15.304 --> 00:37:19.284
So we decided to block the polyamine transporters in dendritic cells using

627
00:37:19.324 --> 00:37:21.364
this specific inhibitor called AMTX.

628
00:37:21.904 --> 00:37:25.604
And as you can see, when we treated dendritic cells with AMTX,

629
00:37:25.944 --> 00:37:29.364
the dendritic cells presented defect in the uptake of the tumor debris.

630
00:37:31.204 --> 00:37:34.824
So now we are trying to understand why the polyamines coming from the tumors

631
00:37:34.984 --> 00:37:36.974
are important for dendritic cells'

632
00:37:38.004 --> 00:37:41.624
uptake. And so far, we found that when dendritic cells

633
00:37:41.984 --> 00:37:45.084
uptake ODC1 knockout tumor debris, first

634
00:37:45.524 --> 00:37:49.404
RAC1 is less expressed, but also RAC1 is less

635
00:37:49.484 --> 00:37:53.104
activated. And giving that RAC1 regulate the actin

636
00:37:53.184 --> 00:37:56.544
polymerization, it suggests a direct link between the

637
00:37:56.564 --> 00:37:59.964
polyamines and the cytoskeleton machinery for uptake.

638
00:38:01.904 --> 00:38:05.404
Then we ask whether the migration is also affected because uptake and

639
00:38:05.444 --> 00:38:09.064
migration are highly linked. When dendritic cells uptake cellular

640
00:38:09.124 --> 00:38:12.964
debris, they quickly migrate. So here we observed

641
00:38:12.984 --> 00:38:16.724
that dendritic cells pulsed with ODC1 knockout tumor

642
00:38:16.764 --> 00:38:20.484
debris, they migrate less to the lymph node compared to the dendritic cells

643
00:38:20.524 --> 00:38:21.084
pulsed with the

644
00:38:22.404 --> 00:38:25.814
wild-type debris. And for the anti-tumor response,

645
00:38:26.264 --> 00:38:30.124
we found that the mice vaccinated with the ODC1 knockout tumor

646
00:38:30.184 --> 00:38:33.864
debris that express OVA developed more B6 synova

647
00:38:33.964 --> 00:38:37.164
tumor compared to the mice vaccinated with the wild-type

648
00:38:37.764 --> 00:38:38.424
tumor debris.

649
00:38:40.304 --> 00:38:44.004
So here we found that the polyamines coming from the tumors are important for

650
00:38:44.064 --> 00:38:47.114
dendritic cells uptake. But what about maturation?

651
00:38:48.334 --> 00:38:51.784
We also found that the dendritic cells have the ability to capture another

652
00:38:51.824 --> 00:38:54.304
metabolite, so here, cholesterol.

653
00:38:54.314 --> 00:38:57.764
So from the tumor, so here we stain the cholesterol in the tumor

654
00:38:58.224 --> 00:39:02.064
using this D4 probe. It's a specific probe for cholesterol.

655
00:39:02.393 --> 00:39:05.984
And as you can see, we were able to detect this cholesterol coming from the

656
00:39:06.004 --> 00:39:08.664
tumor at the surface of the dendritic cells.

657
00:39:10.604 --> 00:39:14.164
So then we ask whether this cholesterol is important for

658
00:39:14.484 --> 00:39:17.824
dendritic cells maturation. And when there is an accumulation of

659
00:39:17.864 --> 00:39:21.024
cholesterol, this cholesterol usually moves to the plasma

660
00:39:21.084 --> 00:39:24.384
membrane through NPC1. So NPC1 binds the

661
00:39:24.404 --> 00:39:27.904
cholesterol in the endolysosomal compartment to regulate its

662
00:39:27.964 --> 00:39:31.384
movement to the plasma membrane. So we ask whether this cholesterol

663
00:39:31.404 --> 00:39:34.433
mobilization is important for dendritic cells maturation.

664
00:39:34.444 --> 00:39:38.184
So we blocked NPC1 activity in dendritic cells, then we

665
00:39:38.244 --> 00:39:42.224
measured the maturation state by looking at the expression of

666
00:39:42.244 --> 00:39:44.164
the different maturation markers.

667
00:39:44.524 --> 00:39:48.184
Here, CCR7 as an example. And as you can see, the

668
00:39:48.204 --> 00:39:51.964
dendritic cells treated with this NPC1 inhibitor express

669
00:39:52.044 --> 00:39:55.844
less CCR7, but we have the same result with the other maturation markers,

670
00:39:56.284 --> 00:40:00.024
suggesting that the cholesterol movement is important for dendritic cells

671
00:40:00.104 --> 00:40:00.704
maturation.

672
00:40:02.404 --> 00:40:05.924
Then we ask whether the internal pool of cholesterol is

673
00:40:05.933 --> 00:40:09.884
important. So we treated the cells with statins to block the synthesis of

674
00:40:09.904 --> 00:40:13.664
cholesterol in dendritic cells. And here, as you can see, the dendritic cells

675
00:40:13.704 --> 00:40:17.484
treated with statins also express less CCR7, but again,

676
00:40:17.544 --> 00:40:20.084
same result with the other maturation markers.

677
00:40:20.094 --> 00:40:23.653
So here it suggests that the cholesterol synthesis and movement are

678
00:40:23.684 --> 00:40:25.844
important for dendritic cells maturation.

679
00:40:26.844 --> 00:40:30.704
But then why? Why this cholesterol movement is important for dendritic

680
00:40:30.744 --> 00:40:34.264
cells maturation? So I told you that the cholesterol moves to the plasma

681
00:40:34.304 --> 00:40:37.624
membrane, and it goes there to form what we call lipid

682
00:40:37.664 --> 00:40:41.384
nanodomains. And these lipid nanodomains are very important for the good

683
00:40:41.484 --> 00:40:45.144
signaling and the good expression of different immunogenic receptors.

684
00:40:45.614 --> 00:40:49.234
So as dendritic cells accumulate cholesterol, we wanted to see whether they

685
00:40:49.324 --> 00:40:51.094
also accumulate lipid nanodomains.

686
00:40:51.664 --> 00:40:55.644
So we stained this structure using cholera toxin B, CTX

687
00:40:55.664 --> 00:40:59.424
B staining. And as you can see, compared to the immature dendritic cells,

688
00:40:59.804 --> 00:41:03.664
mature dendritic cells accumulate these lipid nanodomains at the plasma

689
00:41:03.704 --> 00:41:07.624
membrane. However, when we blocked NPC1 activity or

690
00:41:07.664 --> 00:41:11.114
when we treated the cells with statins, we observed an almost

691
00:41:11.144 --> 00:41:14.824
disappear of these structures, showing the importance of this cholesterol

692
00:41:14.904 --> 00:41:18.364
movement to build these lipid nanodomains at the plasma membrane.

693
00:41:19.784 --> 00:41:23.624
Then we ask whether these lipid nanodomains are important

694
00:41:23.704 --> 00:41:27.454
for dendritic cells maturation. So we decided to destroy these

695
00:41:27.484 --> 00:41:31.324
lipid nanodomains by treating the cells with sphingomyelinase to

696
00:41:31.364 --> 00:41:35.204
remove the sphingomyelin from the

697
00:41:35.224 --> 00:41:38.084
structures, and then we measured the maturation.

698
00:41:38.464 --> 00:41:42.323
And as you can see, the cells treated with sphingomyelinase

699
00:41:42.364 --> 00:41:46.124
expressed less CCR7, but again, same result with the other maturation

700
00:41:46.164 --> 00:41:49.744
markers. So here it suggests that the cholesterol-driven

701
00:41:49.944 --> 00:41:53.464
lipid nanodomains are important for dendritic cells maturation.

702
00:41:54.844 --> 00:41:58.784
So to summarize this part, we found that when dendritic

703
00:41:58.824 --> 00:42:02.324
cells become mature, so when they eat tumor antigen, they

704
00:42:02.404 --> 00:42:06.024
accumulate cholesterol. They take it from the tumor, but also they

705
00:42:06.084 --> 00:42:10.054
increase their own synthesis of cholesterol, and all this

706
00:42:10.084 --> 00:42:14.004
cholesterol moves to the plasma membrane through NPC1 to

707
00:42:14.044 --> 00:42:17.844
form these lipid nanodomains that are important for the good expression,

708
00:42:17.924 --> 00:42:21.854
but also the good signaling of the maturation markers that

709
00:42:21.904 --> 00:42:23.954
are needed to activate the T cells.

710
00:42:25.784 --> 00:42:29.754
So this cholesterol pathway is important for dendritic cells maturation and

711
00:42:29.844 --> 00:42:32.384
function. We wanted to see whether we can boost it.

712
00:42:32.444 --> 00:42:36.304
We can increase the cholesterol level in dendritic cells to boost their

713
00:42:36.324 --> 00:42:39.964
function. So we found that the mature dendritic cells also

714
00:42:40.024 --> 00:42:42.924
express the phagocytic receptor AXL.

715
00:42:43.304 --> 00:42:46.764
And surprisingly, by deleting AXL, dendritic cells

716
00:42:46.824 --> 00:42:50.624
accumulate more cholesterol, as you can see here, but also they

717
00:42:50.684 --> 00:42:52.944
accumulate more lipid nanodomains

718
00:42:53.744 --> 00:42:57.184
at the surface.It was also associated to more

719
00:42:57.204 --> 00:43:00.984
maturation, so here more expression of CCR7, but again,

720
00:43:01.124 --> 00:43:03.064
same result with the other maturation markers.

721
00:43:03.504 --> 00:43:07.144
But when we depleted NPC1 in the AXL knockout, we

722
00:43:07.204 --> 00:43:10.954
observed a decrease of this enhanced maturation, showing

723
00:43:11.004 --> 00:43:14.944
that AXL act through this cholesterol pathway to regulate

724
00:43:14.954 --> 00:43:15.724
the maturation.

725
00:43:17.124 --> 00:43:20.724
And then finally, we asked whether this AXL pathway is relevant for the

726
00:43:20.764 --> 00:43:24.644
anti-tumor immunity. And here, as you can see, the specific deletion

727
00:43:24.684 --> 00:43:28.624
of AXL in the DC compartment decreased the tumor growth, so

728
00:43:28.744 --> 00:43:32.024
less tumor growth suggesting a better anti-tumor response.

729
00:43:34.724 --> 00:43:38.464
So to summarize this part, we found that the mature dendritic cells

730
00:43:38.524 --> 00:43:42.484
also expressed highly AXL, and by blocking AXL, dendritic

731
00:43:42.544 --> 00:43:46.194
cells accumulate more cholesterol, more lipid nanodomain at the

732
00:43:46.264 --> 00:43:49.104
