1369
01:20:32.928 --> 01:20:36.848
microenvironment. Interferon gamma

1370
01:20:36.928 --> 01:20:40.448
is known to reprogram macrophage into an anti-tumor

1371
01:20:40.488 --> 01:20:41.048
phenotype.

1372
01:20:42.228 --> 01:20:46.108
However, it has context-dependent roles and can

1373
01:20:46.148 --> 01:20:49.228
exhibit both pro-tumor and anti-tumor effect,

1374
01:20:50.068 --> 01:20:52.708
depending on the tumor microenvironment.

1375
01:20:53.668 --> 01:20:56.848
So what is its role in the pancreatic cancer?

1376
01:20:58.628 --> 01:21:01.708
First, I analyzed the public human datasets.

1377
01:21:02.708 --> 01:21:05.988
To evaluate the role of interferon gamma in the local tumor

1378
01:21:06.028 --> 01:21:09.848
microenvironment, I focused on non-stage IV cases.

1379
01:21:11.068 --> 01:21:14.988
