1461
01:26:11.252 --> 01:26:15.092
These results indicate that the interferon gamma mediate

1462
01:26:15.212 --> 01:26:18.472
signaling access is conserved across species.

1463
01:26:21.232 --> 01:26:25.032
Given that interferon gamma primarily targets mild cells, we

1464
01:26:25.192 --> 01:26:29.112
next focused on macrophages and performed sub-clustering

1465
01:26:29.192 --> 01:26:29.732
analysis.

1466
01:26:31.412 --> 01:26:34.832
We identified an SPP1 high macrophage

1467
01:26:34.912 --> 01:26:38.592
population that was significantly expanded in knockout

1468
01:26:38.672 --> 01:26:39.132
tumors.

1469
01:26:41.032 --> 01:26:44.432
This population showed reduced interferon gamma

1470
01:26:44.492 --> 01:26:48.272
response and antigen presentation, and increased

1471
01:26:48.332 --> 01:26:50.612
ECM and TGF-beta signaling.

1472
01:26:51.852 --> 01:26:55.552
These results suggest that loss of interferon gamma signaling

1473
01:26:55.752 --> 01:26:59.392
drives macrophage toward a fibrotic and immunosuppressive

1474
01:26:59.512 --> 01:26:59.772
